race.comment: ARIYAH (8) progressed nicely last time out to finish just a long neck from the winner in third over 1100m at Ipswich after being in the firing line on the bend. Plenty of upside and has the class to take this out. BOLD AS BRASS (2) is one from one over this course and distance and has been racing consistently of late. Definite top-three credentials on current form. MR WANDJI (3) has placed four of seven around this circuit, draws low and gets 2kg weight relief with the claim. Ticks a few boxes for a race of this calibre. MISHANI SUSPECT (10) has won when first-up before and can run a race while fresh.
